(11, 'Okanagan Correctional Centre (OCC)', '200 Enterprise Way###Oliver, B.C. VOH 1T2', '236-216-2000', '', '<p>At a cost of nearly 200 million dollars Okanagan Correctional Centre is British Columbia\'s largest and most innovative jail. &nbsp;The jail can house over 700 inmates (primarily male inmates) if necessary, there are over 1,500 cameras in this facility&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Do I need to be on an Incarcerated persons visitors list?&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Yes, the inmate must first put you on a visitors list which takes 1 - 3 business days.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">How can I schedule a visit?<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Call 236-216-2000 press 4 and schedule a visit between the hours of 10AM and 3PM</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Visitation Information:</span>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Length of visit:&nbsp; 60 minutes, must bring at least 1 form of Government Picture ID (passport, driver\'s license, etc.)</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visits per week: &nbsp;2</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visitors per visit: 2 Adults and 2 Children Max.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Can I drop off money to my loved one when I visit? Cash or Money order, no minimum or maximum amount needed &nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Regular Visiting\r\nHours (General Population):</b> </p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" style=\"border: none;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n <tbody><tr>\r\n  <td width=\"91\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:68.4pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt\">\r\n  <p align=\"ce