(39, 'Cape Breton Correctional Facility', '136 Gardiner Road###Sydney, NS B1M 1A1', '902-563-2114', '', '<p>The Cape Breton Correctional Facility was built in 1975 and houses 96 adult male offenders in a medium security Provincial custody setting. &nbsp;Cape Breton Correctional Facility also accommodates upto 4 adult woman and 6 youth temporarily when needed for court appointments.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">Visitation Information:</span>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Length of visit:&nbsp; 1 hr 30 mins</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visits per week: &nbsp;1</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visitors per visit: Upto 5&nbsp; (not including infants)</p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Can I drop off money to my loved one when I visit?Must bring cash (no limit)&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', 'Call ahead, visiting times vary', 'cape-breton-correctional-facility', '20171126102438-capebreton.jpg', 1, '0', '2018-03-20 15:51:41'),
(40, 'Central Nova Scotia Correctional Facility', '90 Gloria McCluskey Ave###Dartmouth, NS B3B 2B9', '902-460-5800', '', '<p>Built in 2001 the Central Nova Scotia Correctional Facility is Nova Scotia\'s largest Provincial Jail. &nbsp;Central Nova Scotia Correctional houses 322 male and 48 female offenders of mainly sentenced and remanded men and women in a medium security Provincial jail setting.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Do I need to be on\r\nan Incarcerated persons visitors list?&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Yes, the inmate must complete a visitor\r\nlist form. You may include up to 10 people on your visitor list (immediate family and upto 2 friends)</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>How can I schedule\r\na visit?<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Incarcerated person will book the visit for you and they\r\nwill be provided a visitation time. Arrive early for your visit. &nbsp;Weekly visits are permitted according to the facility schedule. The superintendent or delegate decides how many visitors are allowed, based on space and your security status.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Visitation\r\nInformation:</b>&nbsp; </p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Length of visit:&nbsp; 60\r\nminutes (varies)</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visits per week: &nbsp;1</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visitors per visit: 4 </p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Can I drop off money to my loved one when I visit?Money\r\ncan be deposited for loved ones via automated teller machines at visit, <b>MUST</b> know Incarcerated persons ID\r\nnumber.</p>', 'Call ahead for visitation times', 'central-nova-scotia-correctional-facility', '20180804100446-central nova scotia.jpg', 1, '0', '2018-03-20 15:51:41'),
