(43, 'Nova Scotia Youth Facility', '1442 County Home Rd###Waterville, NS, B0P 1V0', '902-538-8071', '', '<p><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">The Nova Scotia Youth Facility, located in Waterville, opened in 1988. The provincial facility accommodates male and female young persons serving open or secure custody sentences as well as remanded young persons.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Do I need to be on\r\nan Incarcerated persons visitors list?&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Yes,&nbsp;Visitors permitted include parents/guardians, siblings, children of\r\nthe resident, grandparents, aunts or uncles.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>How can I schedule\r\na visit?<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">For visiting arrangements please telephone 902-538-8071</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Visitation\r\nInformation:</b>&nbsp; </p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Length of visit:&nbsp;\r\nVaries</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visits per week: &nbsp;1 </p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Number of visitors per visit: Residents may receive up to four (4) visitors at one time</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Can I drop off money to my loved one when I visit? Cash, money orders or certified cheques only<b><span style=\"color:#C0504D;mso-themecolor:accent2\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>', 'Each resident is permitted one visit per weekend on Saturday or\r\nSunday from 12:45 p.m. to 3:45 p.m.', 'nova-scotia-youth-facility', '20180804100555-youth detention.jpg', 1, '0', '2018-03-20 15:51:41'),
