(126, 'Joyceville Institution (also known as JAU)', 'Highway 15, PO Box 880###Kingston, ON, K7L 4X9', '1-888-569-2384 ', '', '<p>Joyceville Medium (also known as JAU) was built in 1959. &nbsp;The facility was originally a Federal medium institution but was changed into an assessment unit in 2012. &nbsp;An assessment unit is where most inmates will spend between 3 to 6 months being evaluated until being sent to the institution where they will serve most of their time (known as their \"Mother\" institution). &nbsp;In 2014 Joyceville institution was &nbsp;amalgamated with the Pittsburgh Minimum institution raising Joyceville Institution\'s capacity to 752 adult male Federal inmates.</p><p>Source: &nbsp;http://www.csc-scc.gc.ca/institutions/001002-3007-eng.shtml</p><p style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Do I need to be on\r\nan Incarcerated persons visitors list?&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Yes, visiting application from must be filled out.&nbsp; If there are children visiting then a child\r\nwaiver&nbsp; application must be filled out\r\nfor the child as well.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Click here to download any official visitation\r\nforms:&nbsp;&nbsp;http://www.csc-scc.gc.ca/forms/index-eng.shtml&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>How can I schedule\r\na visit?<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">All visits must be booked at least 48 hours in advance.</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Visitation\r\nInfo